But enough from me.
Let's join the abbotts

697
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:57,700
In camden village.

698
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:18,000
[birds chirping]

699
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,800
[radio static]

700
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:23,400
Oh.

701
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:26,100
Thank you, sweetie.

702
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:31,400
I need to talk to you,

703
00:39:31,600 --> 00:39:33,100
But let's go outside.

704
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:36,300
Oh, sweetie, i'd love to,
But i'm really late.

705
00:39:36,500 --> 00:39:39,000
What's your rush?

706
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:40,300
Surgery.

707
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:42,200
There was that elevator
Disaster downtown.

708
00:39:42,400 --> 00:39:43,700
It was on the news
Last night.

709
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:45,900
This cable just snapped.
This elevator,

710
00:39:46,100 --> 00:39:48,300
It just plummeted down
10 flights.

711
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:49,400
The non-union workers.

712
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:51,600
Just monsters.
You know, that building,

713
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:53,100
It's right next door
To where you work.

714
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:55,200
Can you imagine if you
Had been in there?

715
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,100
It's not even worth
Thinking about.

716
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,100
Anyway,
I have an amputation

717
00:39:58,300 --> 00:40:01,300
On one of the young
Women in that elevator.

718
00:40:01,300 --> 00:40:02,400
She's very young.

719
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:03,300
It's very sad.

720
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:05,400
Anyway, wish me luck.

721
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:08,300
I'll cross my fingers
For you.

722
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,600
[brakes squeal]

723
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:51,200
Uh, excuse me.
Hi. Excuse me.

724
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:53,100
May i help you?

725
00:40:53,300 --> 00:40:53,600
Oh, uh...

726
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:56,800
Yes. I'm looking for my wife,
Nurse burbank.

727
00:40:58,100 --> 00:40:58,600
It's very important.

728
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:01,200
I'm afraid that
That's not possible.

729
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:02,500
She's in pre-op.

730
00:41:02,700 --> 00:41:04,100
Sure.

731
00:41:04,300 --> 00:41:06,000
Ok, fine.

732
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:07,600
Can you pass along a message?

733
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:08,400
I'll try.

734
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:10,300
Can you tell her
I had to go to fiji

735
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:12,100
And that i'll call her
When i get there?

736
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:15,000
When you--
When you get to fiji?

737
00:41:15,300 --> 00:41:15,900
You got it.

738
00:41:16,100 --> 00:41:18,600
Fine. I'll tell her.

739
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:21,100
Thank you so much.

740
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:47,700
Sorry.

741
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:50,300
It's ok.

742
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:58,300
He's here.

743
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:01,700
Meryl: i know, i know.
Shh, shh, shh.

744
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:04,300
Scalpel.

745
00:42:06,100 --> 00:42:08,400
Ahem.

746
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:12,000
I'm now making
My primary incision

747
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:15,900
Just above the right knee.

748
00:42:17,600 --> 00:42:19,900
[loud clang]

749
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:23,000
Nicely done.

750
00:42:23,200 --> 00:42:26,000
This isn't
Going to be pretty.

751
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:28,700
It's just
Beautiful.

752
00:42:28,700 --> 00:42:30,100
Beautiful job.

753
00:42:30,300 --> 00:42:33,300
I'll just let someone else
Tidy up here.

754
00:42:57,700 --> 00:43:00,300
I'm sorry to keep you.

755
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:02,700
Oh, that's ok.

756
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:04,200
How can i help?

757
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,500
I would like to book
A flight to fiji.

758
00:43:06,700 --> 00:43:09,500
When would you like
To leave?

759
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:14,500
Today.

760
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:26,800
[beep]

761
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:27,800
[beep]

762
00:43:28,100 --> 00:43:30,400
[beep]

763
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:31,100
I'm sorry.

764
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:34,300
I don't have anything
For at least a month.

765
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:35,800
A month?

766
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,500
It's the busy season.

767
00:43:39,900 --> 00:43:41,300
You want to book the flight?

768
00:43:41,500 --> 00:43:43,500
It doesn't matter.

769
00:43:43,700 --> 00:43:46,500
I'll make other
Arrangements, ok?

770
00:43:49,700 --> 00:43:52,300
Man:
Last call for chicago!

771
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:55,900
All aboard!

772
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:00,900
[whistles]

773
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:03,400
Thank you.

774
00:44:05,300 --> 00:44:07,900
Windy city, here we come.

775
00:44:09,100 --> 00:44:11,400
Hi.
Hi.

776
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:14,800
Hello.

777
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:17,200
Hi.

778
00:44:17,400 --> 00:44:18,400
Truman: sisters.

779
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:21,100
Hey, mom, isn't that--

780
00:44:21,600 --> 00:44:24,200
Mom: shh.
Face the front.

781
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:34,900
[gears grind]

782
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,600
[gears grind]

783
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,100
[gears grind]

784
00:44:46,300 --> 00:44:47,900
[engine stalls]

785
00:44:48,100 --> 00:44:49,400
[radiator hissing]

786
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:52,400
Everybody off.
We've got a problem.

787
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,500
I'm sorry, son.

788
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:29,100
His father was from
Chicago, wasn't he?

789
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:31,700
No. His dentist
Was from pensacola.

790
00:45:31,900 --> 00:45:33,200
His father
Was from des moines.

791
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:35,300
But how come he wants
To go to chicago?

792
00:45:35,500 --> 00:45:38,600
He's not going to chicago.
He's not going anywhere.

793
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:41,400
  He has to have it out
With meryl.

794
00:45:41,600 --> 00:45:44,000
[pluto barks]

795
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,200
Truman?

796
00:46:03,100 --> 00:46:05,600
Honey, are you ok?

797
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:08,100
Get in.

798
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:12,600
Truman.

799
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,200
Look.

800
00:46:17,900 --> 00:46:20,100
What?
Shh.

801
00:46:20,300 --> 00:46:20,900
I predict

802
00:46:21,100 --> 00:46:22,700
That in just a moment

803
00:46:22,900 --> 00:46:25,700
We will see a lady
On a red bike,

804
00:46:26,500 --> 00:46:28,100
Followed by a man
With flowers

805
00:46:28,300 --> 00:46:30,900
And a volkswagen beetle

806
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:32,400
With a dented fender.

807
00:46:32,600 --> 00:46:34,100
Truman, please.

808
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:36,700
Truman: look.

809
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:42,600
Lady...

810
00:46:43,500 --> 00:46:45,800
Flowers...

811
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:48,300
Both: and...

812
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:51,500
Truman, this is silly.

813
00:46:51,700 --> 00:46:53,000
There it is!
There it is!

814
00:46:53,200 --> 00:46:56,100
  There's that dented
Beetle! Yes!

815
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,700
Aaaaaah!

816
00:46:58,700 --> 00:47:01,100
Ha ha ha!

817
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:04,900
Don't you want to know
How i did that?

818
00:47:04,900 --> 00:47:05,800
I'll tell you.

819
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:06,800
They're on a loop.

820
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:08,400
They go around the block.

821
