Christof: what's he doing
In the basement?

1336
01:13:58,800 --> 01:14:01,800
He moved down there after
Meryl packed up and left.

1337
01:14:02,100 --> 01:14:02,500
Why wasn't i told?

1338
01:14:02,700 --> 01:14:05,700
Any unpredictable behavior
Has to be reported.

1339
01:14:06,400 --> 01:14:09,300
Uh, he--he's just sleeping,
I thought.

1340
01:14:09,500 --> 01:14:11,400
This the best shot
We've got?

1341
01:14:11,600 --> 01:14:12,200
What's to see?

1342
01:14:12,400 --> 01:14:13,400
What's on the clock cam?

1343
01:14:13,600 --> 01:14:16,100
It's an obstruction--
Obstruction.

1344
01:14:16,300 --> 01:14:17,100
What happened down there?

1345
01:14:17,300 --> 01:14:20,100
He was just tidying up
His garbage.

1346
01:14:20,700 --> 01:14:22,500
I was gonna call you,
But halfway through,

1347
01:14:22,700 --> 01:14:24,500
He gave up,
And he fell asleep.

1348
01:14:24,700 --> 01:14:26,600
I wanna check on
The setups for the...

1349
01:14:26,800 --> 01:14:28,300
Both: insurance
Convention tomorrow.

1350
01:14:28,500 --> 01:14:30,900
Yes.
Yeah.

1351
01:14:31,600 --> 01:14:33,100
Nice move.

1352
01:14:33,300 --> 01:14:35,700
[taps keyboard]

1353
01:14:40,200 --> 01:14:41,500
[beep]

1354
01:14:41,700 --> 01:14:44,100
There you go.

1355
01:14:53,000 --> 01:14:55,400
Isolate the audio.

1356
01:14:56,000 --> 01:14:58,300
Give me a closeup
On his torso.

1357
01:14:58,500 --> 01:14:59,300
[beep]

1358
01:14:59,500 --> 01:15:00,200
[snoring]

1359
01:15:00,400 --> 01:15:02,200
He's still breathing.

1360
01:15:02,400 --> 01:15:04,300
[sighs]

1361
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:05,900
Where's chloe?
Yes, sir.

1362
01:15:06,100 --> 01:15:06,500
Call him.

1363
01:15:06,700 --> 01:15:07,600
What do you
Want me to say?

1364
01:15:07,800 --> 01:15:10,200
Tell him
It's a wrong number.

1365
01:15:10,400 --> 01:15:11,300
[chloe dials phone]

1366
01:15:11,500 --> 01:15:13,500
[telephone rings]

1367
01:15:13,800 --> 01:15:14,800
What took you so long?

1368
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:17,800
Just had to wait for it.
They were busy.

1369
01:15:18,300 --> 01:15:19,200
[ring]

1370
01:15:19,400 --> 01:15:20,100
Here.

1371
01:15:20,300 --> 01:15:21,800
What's going on?

1372
01:15:22,000 --> 01:15:23,400
I don't know. They're...

1373
01:15:23,600 --> 01:15:24,100
[ring]

1374
01:15:24,300 --> 01:15:25,200
He came down into the room.

1375
01:15:25,400 --> 01:15:26,900
He did nothing
But stand around for a while.

1376
01:15:27,100 --> 01:15:28,700
Christof:
Shut up and watch it!

1377
01:15:28,900 --> 01:15:30,800
Then we went
To nightvision.

1378
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:32,000
[ring]

1379
01:15:32,200 --> 01:15:33,400
He's asleep.

1380
01:15:33,600 --> 01:15:35,000
[simeon scoffs]

1381
01:15:35,200 --> 01:15:36,000
Christof: there!

1382
01:15:36,200 --> 01:15:37,200
Stop it!
What?

1383
01:15:37,400 --> 01:15:38,100
Zoom in.

1384
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:38,900
On which?

1385
01:15:39,100 --> 01:15:40,100
Under the chair there.

1386
01:15:40,300 --> 01:15:42,700
Simeon: uh-huh.

1387
01:15:43,300 --> 01:15:45,800
Christof: enhance it.

1388
01:15:46,700 --> 01:15:47,900
Simeon: is it--oh.

1389
01:15:48,100 --> 01:15:48,500
Chloe: oh, my god.

1390
01:15:48,700 --> 01:15:51,700
I...if--he couldn't have
Gone up the stairs.

1391
01:15:52,400 --> 01:15:54,000
I definitely--he must
Still be in the room.

1392
01:15:54,300 --> 01:15:55,300
Get marlon
Over there.

1393
01:15:55,500 --> 01:15:56,300
Right away.

1394
01:15:56,500 --> 01:15:58,900
[tires screech]

1395
01:16:02,600 --> 01:16:05,000
[tires screech]

1396
01:16:11,900 --> 01:16:13,600
Marlon: truman!

1397
01:16:13,800 --> 01:16:15,500
Surprise party!

1398
01:16:15,700 --> 01:16:17,100
Oh.

1399
01:16:17,300 --> 01:16:17,900
Come on, buddy.

1400
01:16:18,200 --> 01:16:21,300
I got a 6-pack of cold brewskis
With our name on them.

1401
01:16:21,800 --> 01:16:23,900
Come on, pal.
Come on, buddy.

1402
01:16:24,100 --> 01:16:24,900
[squeak]

1403
01:16:25,100 --> 01:16:27,400
[snoring]

1404
01:16:28,700 --> 01:16:31,000
Shit.

1405
01:16:31,900 --> 01:16:34,800
Marlon, find him.
He's still in the room.

1406
01:16:39,100 --> 01:16:41,300
Come out, come out
Wherever you are.

1407
01:16:41,500 --> 01:16:43,000
That's good.
Keep it light.

1408
01:16:43,200 --> 01:16:46,100
I know you're in here.
I'm gonna find ya.

1409
01:16:50,100 --> 01:16:52,600
Check under the table.

1410
01:16:53,200 --> 01:16:55,700
The closet, behind you.

1411
01:16:59,200 --> 01:17:01,400
Huh.

1412
01:17:02,200 --> 01:17:03,300
Gee.

1413
01:17:03,500 --> 01:17:06,300
I wonder where he
Could possibly be.

1414
01:17:13,700 --> 01:17:16,500
The lawn cam,
Get me the lawn cam.

1415
01:17:23,000 --> 01:17:25,400
Don't look in the camera.
Say something. Keep it going.

1416
01:17:25,600 --> 01:17:27,400
Keep it going.
He's gone.

1417
01:17:27,600 --> 01:17:29,000
Cut transmission!

1418
01:17:29,200 --> 01:17:30,200
Cut transmission?

1419
01:17:30,400 --> 01:17:32,700
Cut it!

1420
01:17:32,900 --> 01:17:33,600
[beep]

1421
01:17:33,900 --> 01:17:34,400
[audience gasps]

1422
01:17:34,600 --> 01:17:35,900
Man: jesus!
God in heaven!

1423
01:17:36,100 --> 01:17:38,000
Woman:
Everything's black.

1424
01:17:38,200 --> 01:17:39,300
Give me the phone.

1425
01:17:39,500 --> 01:17:42,100
[classical music playing]

1426
01:17:49,000 --> 01:17:51,700
[speaking
Various languages]

1427
01:17:52,300 --> 01:17:55,200
I don't know where he is,
But he's gone.

1428
01:18:00,300 --> 01:18:00,700
[clears throat]

1429
01:18:00,900 --> 01:18:03,500
We've got every available
Extra looking for him.

1430
01:18:03,800 --> 01:18:05,300
Uh, the principals
Are helping out.

1431
01:18:05,600 --> 01:18:07,700
The crew, too,
So every sector's covered.

1432
01:18:07,900 --> 01:18:09,600
What about prop cars?

1433
01:18:09,800 --> 01:18:11,600
Yes, they've been
Accounted for.

1434
01:18:11,800 --> 01:18:13,200
He has to be on foot.

1435
01:18:13,400 --> 01:18:15,100
He has the world's
Most recognizable face.

1436
01:18:15,300 --> 01:18:17,800
He can't disappear.

1437
01:18:21,300 --> 01:18:23,600
[siren]

1438
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:48,100
[pluto barking, snarling]

1439
01:18:52,400 --> 01:18:53,800
Spencer: go.

1440
01:18:54,100 --> 01:18:56,100
Hunt him. Hunt him.
Yeah.

1441
01:18:56,400 --> 01:18:57,500
Go find him, pluto.

1442
01:18:57,700 --> 01:18:59,200
Good dog! Good dog!

1443
01:18:59,400 --> 01:19:01,300
All this fuss.

1444
01:19:01,500 --> 01:19:04,200
If he could just
Hear my voice.

1445
01:19:04,900 --> 01:19:07,200
Truman!

1446
01:19:07,500 --> 01:19:08,900
Truman!

1447
01:19:09,100 --> 01:19:10,700
Let me try.

1448
01:19:10,900 --> 01:19:12,300
Truman!

1449
01:19:12,500 --> 01:19:15,000
It's me! Dad!

1450
01:19:16,700 --> 01:19:19,100
Let's talk!

1451
01:19:19,900 --> 01:19:22,300
Yeah, i know.

1452
01:19:22,500 --> 01:19:23,700
Just about done
With the square.

1453
01:19:23,900 --> 01:19:26,900
Got to go back to barrymore,
Check the interiors.

1454
01:19:27,100 --> 01:19:28,100
He's got to be in there.

1455
01:19:28,400 --> 01:19:29,600
Simeon:
Barrymore, huh?

1456
01:19:29,800 --> 01:19:30,000
Uh-huh.

1457
01:19:30,200 --> 01:19:32,100
But what about the college?
Who's watching that?

1458
01:19:32,300 --> 01:19:32,700
I don't know.

1459
01:19:32,900 --> 01:19:34,200
Send somebody
Over there, ok?

1460
01:19:34,400 --> 01:19:36,800
All right.

1461
01:19:39,900 --> 01:19:41,700
Take another man and get
Down there now, all right?

1462
01:19:41,900 --> 01:19:43,800
I don't give a damn. Just
Find the son of a bitch.

1463
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:47,000
Get some batteries. This guy's
Not gonna glow in the dark.

1464
01:19:47,200 --> 01:19:47,800
Just get 'em down here.

1465
01:19:48,000 --> 01:19:51,100
I don't know what's going
On. Reroute it back to me.

1466
01:19:51,200 --> 01:19:52,000
We need more light.

1467
01:19:52,200 --> 01:19:54,900
We'll never find him
This way.

1468
01:20:00,000 --> 01:20:01,300
What time is it?

1469
01:20:01,500 --> 01:20:04,200
It's way too early
For that.

1470
01:20:10,700 --> 01:20:13,100
Cue the sun.

1471
01:20:15,400 --> 01:20:17,600
[people gasp]

1472
01:20:17,800 --> 01:20:18,400
Jeez!

1473
01:20:18,600 --> 01:20:20,700
What time is it?

1474
01:20:20,900 --> 01:20:21,700
Christof,
What's going on?

1475
01:20:21,900 --> 01:20:24,300
Did you know that there's
A rumor circulating

1476
01:20:24,500 --> 01:20:26,600
That he's dead?
You hear me?

1477
01:20:26,800 --> 01:20:29,300
The media is having
A feeding frenzy over this.

1478
01:20:29,500 --> 01:20:30,900
All the phone lines
Are jammed,

1479
01:20:31,200 --> 01:20:32,900
And every network has
A pirated shot of marlon

1480
01:20:33,200 --> 01:20:34,500
Making an ass of himself
In front of the camera.

1481
01:20:34,700 --> 01:20:36,800
The sponsors are threatening
To rip up their contracts.

1482
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:38,700
Why? We're getting higher
Ratings with this graphic

1483
01:20:38,900 --> 01:20:41,700
Than we've ever had
On this show.

1484
01:20:45,500 --> 01:20:45,900
No sign of him.

1485
01:20:46,100 --> 01:20:49,000
Why don't you head back
To town and join the others?

1486
01:20:49,200 --> 01:20:52,100
Everyone else is
At first positions, ok?

1487
01:20:52,100 --> 01:20:52,900
Thank you.

1488
01:20:53,100 --> 01:20:56,000
Everyone's at first
Positions, right?

1489
01:21:11,600 --> 01:21:12,700
Simeon:
We've got the light.

1490
01:21:12,900 --> 01:21:15,700
So he's got to
Be there somewhere.

1491
01:21:18,000 --> 01:21:19,200
We're not
Watching the sea.

1492
01:21:19,400 --> 01:21:22,500
Simeon: hang on a minute.
Why would we watch the sea?

1493
01:21:23,100 --> 01:21:24,200
Sweep the harbor.

1494
01:21:24,400 --> 01:21:25,100
Bring up the harbor cameras.

1495
01:21:25,300 --> 01:21:27,900
Shift all harbor cameras
To computer, please.

1496
01:21:28,100 --> 01:21:29,600
Some of those are out,
Aren't they?

1497
01:21:29,800 --> 01:21:31,000
Operator: yeah.
We have 4 of them down,

1498
01:21:31,200 --> 01:21:33,300
But we have
The lighthouse cameras up.

1499
01:21:33,600 --> 01:21:34,800
All buoy cams, please.

1500
01:21:35,000 --> 01:21:35,600
Moses:
What's happening?

1501
01:21:35,800 --> 01:21:38,700
Operator: ok. Long lens,
Short base cameras.

1502
01:21:38,800 --> 01:21:41,400
Moses: why are we
Looking at the water?

1503
01:21:41,600 --> 01:21:44,400
Operator: pan it,
Will you, please?

1504
01:21:46,600 --> 01:21:48,900
Truman...

1505
01:21:49,900 --> 01:21:52,400
Where are you going?

1506
01:21:52,600 --> 01:21:54,600
How can he sail?
He's in insurance.

1507
01:21:54,800 --> 01:21:56,200
Operator: isn't he
Terrified of the water?

1508
01:21:56,400 --> 01:21:57,200
Resume transmission.

1509
01:21:57,400 --> 01:21:59,900
Resuming transmission.

1510
01:22:04,700 --> 01:22:05,800
I got 2 to 1
He doesn't make it.

1511
01:22:06,000 --> 01:22:07,900
Man: hey, i want
A piece of that.

1512
01:22:08,100 --> 01:22:09,900
2 to 1
He doesn't make it.

1513
01:22:10,100 --> 01:22:11,500
[key tapping]

1514
01:22:11,800 --> 01:22:14,000
Just leave 'em
In the car.

1515
01:22:14,200 --> 01:22:16,500
Shh.

1516
01:22:26,500 --> 01:22:27,800
Let's get off
This mast shot.

1517
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:30,400
We can't see his face.
Go to the cabin cam.

1518
01:22:30,600 --> 01:22:32,900
Cabin cam.

1519
01:22:34,300 --> 01:22:36,000
There. Perfect.

1520
01:22:36,200 --> 01:22:38,700
That's our hero shot.

1521
01:23:03,600 --> 01:23:05,400
Let's get another boat
Out there.

1522
01:23:05,600 --> 01:23:08,400
Ok. Listen, gus, i need you to
Talk to the guys on the ferry.

1523
01:23:08,600 --> 01:23:11,600
Come on. Get it moving.
Get it out of here.

1524
01:23:11,900 --> 01:23:13,900
[grinding]

1525
01:23:14,200 --> 01:23:15,100
Gus: come on.

1526
01:23:15,300 --> 01:23:16,200
I'm just a bus driver.

1527
01:23:16,400 --> 01:23:19,300
Bottom line is,
They can't drive the boat.

1528
01:23:19,500 --> 01:23:21,900
They're actors.

1529
01:23:24,500 --> 01:23:27,000
How do we stop him?

1530
01:23:37,200 --> 01:23:39,500
Ok, uh...

1531
01:23:40,100 --> 01:23:43,200
We're going to be accessing
The weather program now.

1532
01:23:44,500 --> 01:23:46,800
So hold on to your hats.

1533
01:23:47,000 --> 01:23:48,300
You got that?

1534
01:23:48,500 --> 01:23:51,600
No. I think we're gonna
Want to localize the storm

1535
01:23:52,500 --> 01:23:54,900
Over the boat.

1536
01:23:56,300 --> 01:23:57,900
You can get
The coordinates for that.

1537
01:23:58,200 --> 01:24:00,900
There's no rescue boat.
He won't know what to do.

1538
01:24:01,200 --> 01:24:04,000
He'll turn back.
He'll be too afraid.

1539
01:24:04,000 --> 01:24:06,300
[whispering]

1540
01:24:06,600 --> 01:24:09,000
There she blows.

1541
01:24:19,200 --> 01:24:20,300
[motor stalling]

1542
01:24:20,600 --> 01:24:22,800
Come on.

1543
01:24:45,000 --> 01:24:46,400
Give me some lightning.

1544
01:24:46,600 --> 01:24:47,900
[thunder]

1545
01:24:48,100 --> 01:24:49,500
Again!

1546
01:24:49,700 --> 01:24:52,100
Hit him again!

1547
01:25:02,100 --> 01:25:04,600
For god's sake, christof,
The whole world is watching.

1548
01:25:04,800 --> 01:25:06,300
We can't let him die
In front of a live audience.

1549
01:25:06,600 --> 01:25:09,400
He was born in front
Of a live audience.

1550
01:25:37,800 --> 01:25:38,700
[cheering]

1551
01:25:38,900 --> 01:25:41,200
Truman!

1552
01:25:43,100 --> 01:25:45,700
You can do it!
Hold on!

1553
01:26:10,300 --> 01:26:13,000
Is that the best
You can do?

1554
01:26:13,900 --> 01:26:16,600
You're gonna have
To kill me!

1555
01:26:17,900 --> 01:26:20,000
 What shall we do
With a drunken sailor 

1556
01:26:20,200 --> 01:26:20,700
On behalf of the studio,

1557
01:26:20,900 --> 01:26:22,300
I demand that you
Cease transmission.

1558
01:26:22,500 --> 01:26:23,000
Keep running.

1559
01:26:23,200 --> 01:26:25,200
 What shall we do
With a drunken sailor 

1560
01:26:25,400 --> 01:26:27,500
 Early in the mornin'? 

1561
01:26:27,700 --> 01:26:29,500
Increase the wind.

1562
01:26:29,700 --> 01:26:30,300
Increase the wind!

1563
01:26:30,600 --> 01:26:33,200
[truman
Continues singing]

1564
01:26:33,400 --> 01:26:34,700
I'm telling you
For the last time.

1565
01:26:34,900 --> 01:26:35,900
How close is he?
Very.

1566
01:26:36,100 --> 01:26:37,300
Capsize him.
Tip him over.

1567
01:26:37,500 --> 01:26:38,100
Damn you,
Christof!

1568
01:26:38,300 --> 01:26:39,900
You can't. He's tied
Himself to the boat!

1569
01:26:40,100 --> 01:26:40,300
Shut up!

1570
01:26:40,500 --> 01:26:42,700
He's gonna drown,
And he doesn't even care.

1571
01:26:42,900 --> 01:26:44,400
Do it.
No.

1572
01:26:44,600 --> 01:26:46,800
Do it!

1573
01:27:29,800 --> 01:27:32,100
[thunder]

1574
01:27:39,300 --> 01:27:41,700
That's enough.

1575
01:28:11,400 --> 01:28:13,700
[gagging]

1576
01:29:31,200 --> 01:29:33,500
[crash]

1577
01:30:00,300 --> 01:30:02,500
Oh.

1578
01:30:03,700 --> 01:30:05,900
Oh.

1579
01:31:51,400 --> 01:31:54,200
Christof:
I want to talk to him.

1580
01:32:12,500 --> 01:32:13,300
Truman.

1581
01:32:13,500 --> 01:32:14,300
[gasps]

1582
01:32:14,500 --> 01:32:16,900
You can speak.

1583
01:32:17,700 --> 01:32:20,400
[over speaker]
I can hear you.

1584
01:32:24,500 --> 01:32:25,000
Who are you?

1585
01:32:25,200 --> 01:32:27,200
I am the creator
Of a television show

1586
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:30,600
That gives hope and joy
And inspiration to millions.

1587
01:32:36,200 --> 01:32:37,500
Then who am i?

1588
01:32:37,700 --> 01:32:40,100
You're the star.

1589
01:32:45,400 --> 01:32:47,100
Was nothing real?

1590
01:32:47,300 --> 01:32:48,100
You were real.

1591
01:32:48,300 --> 01:32:51,100
That's what made you
So good to watch.

1592
01:32:52,100 --> 01:32:54,200
Listen to me, truman.

1593
01:32:54,400 --> 01:32:56,800
There's no more truth
Out there...

1594
01:32:57,000 --> 01:33:00,000
Than there is in the world
I created for you.

1595
01:33:02,500 --> 01:33:05,000
The same lies.

1596
01:33:05,900 --> 01:33:07,600
The same deceit.

1597
01:33:07,800 --> 01:33:10,300
But in my world...

1598
01:33:11,500 --> 01:33:14,200
